{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/mathematics-visualizations/","result":{"data":{"post":{"id":"0cb3da46-ca79-5db6-ac0f-8282c6027fae","html":"<h3>The Beauty of Pi</h3>\n<p>\n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 95.59559559559561%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"The Beauty of Pi\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/Bootstrap-portfolio/static/3e13f765330fc12e7b4f963a608b3623/5a190/pi.png\"\n        srcset=\"/Bootstrap-portfolio/static/3e13f765330fc12e7b4f963a608b3623/772e8/pi.png 200w,\n/Bootstrap-portfolio/static/3e13f765330fc12e7b4f963a608b3623/e17e5/pi.png 400w,\n/Bootstrap-portfolio/static/3e13f765330fc12e7b4f963a608b3623/5a190/pi.png 800w,\n/Bootstrap-portfolio/static/3e13f765330fc12e7b4f963a608b3623/20c85/pi.png 999w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \nWhen I started to redesign my website I knew I wanted to update my background and add some cool visuals and I didn’t want to be too cheesy.  So no space themed backgrounds no matter how much they kind of appealed to me.  I decided to try to find some cool open source math visualizations because well Math is cool.  While I was looking I found this really cool website that had just hosts of awesome math and data visualizations.  The site was <a href=\"https://www.flerlagetwins.com/\">“The Ferlange Twins”</a> and is just a site for Ken and Kevin Ferlange to share their cool data visualizations and Tableau projects like the amazing visualization of the first 5000 digits of pi by Ken that I have above.</p>\n<p>Exporing their site I found a lot of really awesome data visualizations including one that looked at the incidence and impact of tornados over time which I will go ahead and link <a href=\"https://www.flerlagetwins.com/2020/01/new-viz-tornado.html\">here</a>.  I have never used Tableau before but I am really impressed with what the Ferlange twins can do with it.  Maybe I’ll have to add this to my continuously growing list of cool stuff to learn.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/mathematics-visualizations/","prefix":"2020-24-01"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Mathematical Visualizations","author":"tierra farris","category":"cool things","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/3e13f765330fc12e7b4f963a608b3623/630fb/pi.png"}}}}},"authornote":{"id":"1be9f1c1-5e8a-5240-bdb2-cb2b9320b44e","html":"<p><strong>Tierra Farris</strong> Former biologist, fledgling computer scientist and whole-hearted science fiction nerd.</p>"},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"facebook":{"appId":"..."}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/mathematics-visualizations/","prev":{"id":"10589bd6-b631-5c6a-8b43-eae48205ce9c","fields":{"slug":"/i-love-graphs-or-just-because-someone-said-it-on-medium-doesn't-mean-it's-true copy/","prefix":"2020-12-02","source":"posts"},"frontmatter":{"title":"I Love Graphs","category":"cool things"}},"source":"posts"}}}